THIRD-PARTY DEPENDENCIES (not redistributed; resolved at install time)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Aughor depends on packages fetched from PyPI and the npm registry at install
time. They are not included in this repository. Their licenses are recorded in
`uv.lock` and `web/package-lock.json`.

Two dependency licenses are worth calling out for redistributors:

  * psycopg2-binary / psycopg  — LGPL-3.0. Imported as a library; not modified
    and not statically linked into Aughor. Aughor's own Apache-2.0 terms are
    unaffected. If you redistribute a bundled artifact, preserve the users'
    ability to relink against a modified psycopg.

  * text-unidecode — Artistic-1.0 / GPL. Reached only through the optional
    `evals` extra (via python-slugify). It is NOT installed by a default
    `uv sync`. Avoid the `evals` extra if GPL-adjacent code in your dependency
    closure is a problem for you.
